<h2>The weather in May 2021</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
<br><br>
The monthly mean temperature for May was lower than normal over large parts of Europe (Figure 4). Exceptionally below average maximum temperatures occurred over the Czech Republic and Austria (see Figure 5) where temperatures were more than 2 &deg;C below normal. Southerwestern and the eastern parts of Europe, on the contrary, saw warmer than normal mean temperatures in May. Over Iberia and eastern parts of Russia both minimum and mean temperatures were even exceptionally above average with temperatures locally around 2&deg;C above the long-term average.
<br><br>
<a href="../images/may2021/Stateofclimate_May2021_tn_0_25deg_anom_monthlymeans_2021_1981-2010_v22_0e_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_tn_baselayers_overlay_2021-05-31T00-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/may2021/Stateofclimate_May2021_tn_0_25deg_anom_monthlymeans_2021_1981-2010_v22_0e_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_tn_baselayers_overlay_2021-05-31T00-00-00Z.png" ></a>
